      <p class="step-label">Step 6 of 9</p>
      <h1>Set Up a Workspace</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Establish a dedicated space for building and testing your robot.</p>
      <section class="content-section">
        <p>A workspace does not have to be fancy, but it should be safe, organized, and available often enough for the team to build consistently. Tables, power access, storage, and basic tools matter more than square footage.</p>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Workspace basics</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Room for a build table and a laptop or programming station</li>
            <li>Storage for parts, batteries, chargers, and notebooks</li>
            <li>Clear rules for cleanup, tool use, and safety gear</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Pick one regular meeting spot and make sure the sponsor or mentor can help supervise access there.</p>
      </section>
      <div class="step-actions">
        <a href="/start-team-step7" class="btn btn-primary">Next: Get Equipment & Parts →</a>
